    {
      "id": "translation",
      "html": "<h2>English translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\"><a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag</a></p>  <p>To [---]a Procula, daughter of Lucius... [(name)] Plaetorius, son of Spurius, of the Claudian tribe, quaestor, aedile, duumvir, ... [(name) --]ius Galeo, son of Quintus, of the Quirina tribe, to whom the decurial order decreed aedilician honours, [---]a Longina, daughter of Lucius. [(name)] Proculus, of the Claudian tribe, quaestor four times, prefect pro duumvir, duumvir quinqennalis, military tribune of the Legio VI Ferrata. </p>  "
    },
    {
      "id": "commentary",
      "html": "<h2>commentary</h2>  <p>  </p>  "
    },
    {
      "id": "bibliography",
      "html": "<h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li> 1976.0265 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283</a>  </li><li> Bivona 1976 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002139\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002139</a>  </li><li> Manganaro 1988 42 n.209, 43, 45 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001427\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001427</a>  </li><li> Wilson 1990 173 fig.145 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001509\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001509</a>  </li><li> Bivona 1994 15 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002137\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002137</a>  </li><li> Gregori 2012 315-318 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002594\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002594</a>  </li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  "
    },
    {
      "id": "handnote",
      "html": " <p>Tall letters, showing some narrowness/compression in the module; occasional use of ligature and hedera, with a distinctive form of the letter G. Note that the final three lines appear to be in a different hand, less regular, with a different interpunct, differences notable in e.g. E, G and R.</p> Line 1  73-75  Line 2  38-40  Line 3  38-42  Line 4  35-39  Line 5  44-47  Interlineation line 1 to 2      <p>The final three lines appear to be in a different hand, less regular, with a different interpunct, differences notable in e.g. E, G and R.</p> Line 6  27-35  Line 7  34-38  Line 8  28-31  "
    },
